    <body>
        <div class="note">
            <p class="noteInDiv" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #6dc1aa;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If you do not update your source templates (or if your import a Word document from an older Doc-To-Help project), you may see two Doc-To-Help ribbons in Word. This occurs when you are working in a Word document based on a template that contains macros while you are simultaneously using the latest version of Doc-To-Help (which uses the Doc-To-Help Word add-in to open the Doc-To-Help ribbon).</p>
            <p class="Final">To resolve this, you should update your source document's template. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineOnly"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../D2H/Templates/Selecting-Templates-D2H.htm">Selecting Templates</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.PrintOnly"> See the online Help or the <span class="EmphasisItalic">Making It Look Good Guide</span>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
        </div>
